body:
- VSCode Version: v1.28.0
- OS Version: macOS v10.13.5

The following extension takes about 260ms on my machine to execute:

```ts
const start = Date.now ();

import * as globby from 'globby';

const activate = function ( context: vscode.ExtensionContext ) {
  globby;
};

export {activate};

const end = Date.now ();
const elapsed = end - start;
import * as vscode from 'vscode';
vscode.window.showInformationMessage ( `Elapsed: ${elapsed}ms` );
```

While executing the compiled JS directly from node (v8.4.0 and v10.11.0) takes about half as much, 130ms:

```js
"use strict";
Object.defineProperty(exports, "__esModule", { value: true });
const start = Date.now();
const globby = require("globby");
const activate = function (context) {
    globby;
};
exports.activate = activate;
const end = Date.now();
const elapsed = end - start;
console.log(`Elapsed: ${elapsed}ms`);
//# sourceMappingURL=extension.js.map
```

Maybe this is normal, but you might want to take a look into this.
